{
  "texts": [
    "For counterfactual explanations, popular properties are proximity, sparsity, and plausibility (Verma et al. 2020).",
    "Proximity is a property that is somehow used in every counterfactual algorithm.",
    "It tries to measure the total change that is suggested by the counterfactual explanations with a distance metric (typically L1 or L2 distance) (Van Looveren and Klaise 2021; Mothilal et al. 2020; Wexler et al. 2019).",
    "It is intuitive that less change is better than more change in most situations.",
    "Sparsity is a special case of proximity."
  ]
}